content:
Assassination classroom is by far one of the best animes I have ever watched! I Would recommend it to anyone and everyone!Its a must watch anime and it deserves to be one.
{Spoilers}
{Story 9/10}
Story wise it was amazing! They spread it out so it didn't feel rushed and instead of forcing you to enjoy the anime, it allowed you too. It really made me feel like I was apart of the classroom and thats not just my opinion.
The reason the story is a 9/10 though is because of the protagonist and some of the vocab they used. They call the classroom assassination classroom when they aren'treally killing anyone. They say they are assassins but never hurt anyone until the last episode. They have a target so technically they are, but still makes me wish they had a different name that would be more fitting for the anime.


Second point is Nagisa. They say he has a talent for assassination but they only show that talent 4-5 times! I wish they had more battle scenes because i was somewhat deprived of them. 


{Art 10/10}

Amazing art! At first I watched the anime because it reminded me of Danganronpa and I thought thats why I liked the anime. But after getting to the second season i realized thats not the case. It unique the art and the character designs are so so so cute/hot *cough*.


{Sound 10/10}

The music was Incredible!

The openings are so catchy and cute and I love them! And the sad music at the end just made the feels even bigger!


{Character 10/10}

Amazing characters! I love them all! Nagisa, Karma, Koro-Sensei, Bitch Sensei. They really make it feel like its a classroom. They focus on ever character, and give a lot of them some screen time. They only thing I wish was that they showed more of the actual protagonists and maybe a little bit less of the side characters.


{Enjoyment 10/10}

I Loved this anime! I didn't feel bored and I watched it for 2 days straight. When i was at school the only thing I really though about was going home and continuing watching it! It hits you with the feel at the end and was one anime that left me sobbing. And when ever i think about it i still feel like sobbing. Its just so good.


{Overall 10/10}

Amazing anime! I wish it showed more of Nagisa, and sometimes i wish it never ended but I know that would ruin the anime. It actually followed through with the main plot unlike a lot of western tv shows and movies.


Please watch it you shall not be disappointed! :3
